main event: A bright, luminous, oblong object was observed hovering over a wooded area near Palatka, Florida on July 8, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 10 minutes before it disappeared.
The witness was unable to provide details about the size, altitude, or speed of the object.
The case was investigated but no further information was developed to identify the object.
The report mentions seeing other lights in the sky that night, in addition to the main object.
The object was described as round, large, and silvery, and it maneuvered rapidly before disappearing.
